.SH NAME
FontFace.FontFace \- FontFace: FontFace() constructor
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]FontFace()\f[B]\f[R] constructor creates a new
\f[CR]FontFace\f[R] object.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
new FontFace(family, source)
new FontFace(family, source, descriptors)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]family\f[R]
Specifies a font family name that can be used to match against this font
face when styling elements.
.RS
.PP
Takes the same type of values as the \f[CR]font\-family\f[R] descriptor
of \f[CR]\[at]font\-face\f[R].
This value may also be read and set using the \f[CR]FontFace.family\f[R]
property.
.RE
.TP
\f[B]source\f[R]
The font source.
This can be either:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
A URL to a font face file.
.IP \[bu] 2
Binary font face data in an \f[CR]ArrayBuffer\f[R] or a
\f[CR]TypedArray\f[R].
.RE
.TP
\f[B]descriptors\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A set of optional descriptors passed as an object.
It can contain any of the descriptors available for
\f[CR]\[at]font\-face\f[R]:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]ascentOverride\f[R]
With an allowable value for \f[CR]\[at]font\-face/ascent\-override\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]descentOverride\f[R]
With an allowable value for
\f[CR]\[at]font\-face/descent\-override\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]display\f[R]
With an allowable value for \f[CR]\[at]font\-face/font\-display\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]featureSettings\f[R]
With an allowable value for \f[CR]font\-feature\-settings\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]lineGapOverride\f[R]
With an allowable value for
\f[CR]\[at]font\-face/line\-gap\-override\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]stretch\f[R]
With an allowable value for \f[CR]\[at]font\-face/font\-stretch\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]style\f[R]
With an allowable value for \f[CR]\[at]font\-face/font\-style\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]unicodeRange\f[R]
With an allowable value for \f[CR]\[at]font\-face/unicode\-range\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]variationSettings\f[R]
With an allowable value for
\f[CR]\[at]font\-face/font\-variation\-settings\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]weight\f[R]
With an allowable value for \f[CR]\[at]font\-face/font\-weight\f[R].
.RE
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]SyntaxError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown when a descriptor string does not match the grammar of the
corresponding \f[CR]\[at]font\-face\f[R] descriptor, or the specified
binary source cannot be loaded.
This error results in \f[CR]FontFace.status\f[R] being set to
\f[CR]error\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]async\f[R] \f[B]function\f[R] loadFonts() {
  \f[B]const\f[R] font = \f[B]new\f[R] FontFace(\[dq]my\-font\[dq], \[dq]url(my\-font.woff)\[dq], {
